node.text:
Video tour of The Syshaus designed by @studio.arthurcasas.

The Syshaus is the future of housing. It is a concept with constructive system with a standardized 1.2m grid system that allows the house to be built within 6 months. The keywords are quality, practicality, and sustainability, and eliminates the hassle of constructing a house.

node.text:
Who’d you bring? 💚
Constructed as a movie set for the Lord of the Rings movies, Hobbiton displays a soulful type of vernacular architecture giving life to organic, circular shapes that follows Matamata’s grassy hills of the northern part of New Zealand. In regular urban and suburban areas, we tend to live in boxes; most of them being rather identical. Hobbiton therefore proposes a great alternative and an example of what architecture can become to allow an immersive experience of nature. // Photos by @shaun_jeffers.

Watch more house tours on our new YouTube channel. 🎥
Link in bio!

node.text:
Who’d want to live here? 😍
This Scandinavian loft has an exposed brick wall partly dividing the kitchen space and the living room, yet allowing free movement and openness. The wall gives a very distinctive aesthetic with a rustic feel, which at the same time creates a more artistic atmosphere. The loft is designed by @lovewarriors and is located in Stockholm, Sweden // Photos by @elisabethphotography.

Watch more house tours on our new YouTube channel. 🎥
Link in bio!

node.text:
The Oxygen House is a contemporary home using a palette of natural materials to reference the tones and textures of its natural setting. All the rooms have been designed as cubes linked together by glass passages to create a feeling of strolling through a forest. The house is designed by @susannacots and is located in Emporda, Spain // Photos by Mauricio Fuertes.

Watch more house tours on our new YouTube channel. 🎥

Conceptualized for a plot in the northern part of Iran, this modern residence balances a symphony of dark, earthy tones to create a calm but contemporary home with direct access to its natural environment. Surrounded by tall trees, the  residence effectively simulates a private enclave. It is designed and visualized by @bahman_behzadi_art.

node.text:
Swipe left! What do you think? 😍
The Lawless Retreat is a forest residence tugged between trees along the edge of a state park. The Chicago-based couple had searched five years across four states to find a site for their weekend home, finally falling in love with the calm Michigan nature. With a mix of contemporary and rustic elements, the home beautifully balances the clean and raw. The house is designed by @searllamasterhowe and is located in Jones, Michigan // Photos by @soluriphoto.

Watch more house tours on our new YouTube channel. 🎥
Link in bio!

How amazing is this? 💙
SJA III House is a residence determined to emerge from the relationship with our primeval home: the earth. Guided by the natural, rocky characteristics and topography, the house ignores defined human space, fully integrating the living experience with its context. The house is designed by @cdmcasasdemexico and is located in // Photos by @arorygardiner.

Watch more house tours on our new YouTube channel. 🎥

node.text:
Swipe left! What do you think? 😍
The RLW House is a 914 sqm. home situated in the dense Atlantic Forest vegetation. One of the main focus points was to minimise the home’s footprint on the landscape, which meant that the house had to be placed as subtly as possible. Despite the five floors, the house only appears to be two-storeys, which is considered to be aesthetically more appropriate for a beach house. The house is designed by @jacobsenarquitetura and is located in Guaruja, Brazil // Photos by @leonardofinotti.

Watch more house tours on our new YouTube channel. 🎥
Link in bio!

The S.A. Residence is a three-story cast-concrete home with a water-court swimming pond to ensure privacy. with a simple architectural aesthetic, the home is made to fit its rural urban environment. The house is designed by Shatotto and is located in Dhaka, Bangladesh // Photos by Daniele Domenicali.

Watch more house tours on our new YouTube channel. 🎥

node.text:
Who’d you bring? 💙
The Stella Island Resort is a retreat where all buildings are in direct contact with water which gives the impression of a floating hotel. The rooms have a small wooden deck functioning as verandas and with direct access to the Laguna pool. The hotel is characterized by natural materials which are present throughout the design. The retreat is designed by Stavros Peppas Architect & Partners and is located in Crete, Greece // Photos by @travel.for.memory.

Watch more house tours on our new YouTube channel. 🎥

node.text:
Day or night? 🤔
Arcadia is a contemporary home with a volumetric style where stacked cubes and an overhang roof present a playful exterior. By adding vegetation to the floating balconies, it makes the facade come alive while complementing the wooden details. The house is designed by @line_and_space_ and is located in Chandigarh, India // Video by @line_and_space_.

Watch more house tours on our new YouTube channel. 🎥
Link in bio!

node.text:
Swipe left! What do you think? 😍
This Scandinavian home is situated with views overlooking the absolutely stunning natural landscape of the Norwegian archipelago. At the same time, the elevated plot gives the real impression of the magnitude of the surrounding environment. With its minimalistic coziness and attention to detail, the house showcase what it essentially means to live in a modern Nordic home. The house is self-designed by @maritfolland and is located in Averøy, Norway // Photos and video by @maritfolland.

Watch more house tours on our new YouTube channel. 🎥
Link in bio!

Chaká House is a tropical home placed in an urban area in the northern part of Merida, Mexico. Designed as an oasis, the three-volume house points attention to the incredible central courtyard, allowing the interior spaces to be flooded with natural light and a comfortable breeze. The house is designed by @quesnelarqs // Photos by @manolorsolis_fotografia.
